Let's think step by step. We can use the fact that the sum of the interior angles of any triangle is $180^{\circ}$ to find the measure of $\angle AHC$. Therefore, $\angle AHC = 180-(\angle CAH+\angle HCA)$. From our earlier work, $\angle CAH=90^{\circ}$ and $\angle CHA=180^{\circ}-\angle CBA-\angle CAB=180^{\circ}-52^{\circ}-54^{\circ}=74^{\circ}$. Thus, $\angle AHC = 180^{\circ} - 90^{\circ} - 74^{\circ} = 16^{\circ}.$ Now, since $\overline{AH}\perp\overline{BC},$ we have that $\angle ABH=90^{\circ}.$ Now we can compute the value of $\angle AHB$: \begin{align*}
\angle AHB&=\angle ABH+\angle BHA\\
&=90^{\circ}+16^{\circ}\\
&=\boxed{106^{\circ}}
\end{align*}The answer is: 106°.
